From 7d8938969a755d640a79ea318e712fa3b6771346 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ram <chan2006@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Jul 2026 04:56:40 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add Knowledge Base pre-check: block critical-risk Terraform
 on upload
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Addresses the 'garbage in, garbage out' enterprise gap: Terraform
templates uploaded to the Knowledge Base are used as a trusted
baseline pattern for every future blueprint, so an insecure upload
would silently replicate that vulnerability across an organisation.

- lib/agents/kb-auditor.ts: new agent, same pattern as the existing
  Gatekeeper/Auditor agents. Scans .tf content for genuinely critical
  issues only (hardcoded secrets, publicly-accessible databases/
  storage, wildcard IAM policies, explicitly disabled encryption) —
  deliberately narrow scope so it doesn't block legitimate templates
  over style or best-practice nitpicks.
- app/api/knowledge-base/scan/route.ts: authenticated API route.
  Only runs the scan for .tf files; other KB document types (PDFs,
  naming convention docs) pass through unchanged. Fails open (does
  not block upload) if the scan call itself errors, so an Anthropic
  API hiccup can't take down KB uploads entirely — worth revisiting
  if a stricter fail-closed posture is wanted for compliance.
- components/knowledge-base/KnowledgeBaseClient.tsx: .tf uploads
  now route through the scan before reaching storage. Blocked
  uploads show a clear banner listing each specific issue found
  (resource + description), not just a generic rejection toast.

Verified: tsc --noEmit clean, next build succeeds (24/24 pages,
new /api/knowledge-base/scan route confirmed), no new lint errors
(3 pre-existing issues in the touched file confirmed via diff
against HEAD — unrelated to this change).
